          'Day six is a western excursion to the ancient city of Kutaisi and the spectacular canyons of the Imereti region. Visit the UNESCO-listed Gelati Monastery, explore the stunning Prometheus Cave with its underground rivers and lake, and walk the dramatic hanging walkway of the Okatse Canyon. Return to Tbilisi in the evening, or alternatively, stay in Kutaisi if you are flying out from its international airport.',
          'Day seven offers a relaxed morning in Tbilisi for last-minute shopping and sightseeing. Visit the Dry Bridge flea market for unique souvenirs, explore the Dezerter Bazaar for local food products, or simply enjoy a leisurely breakfast at one of the city\'s excellent cafes. This itinerary can be customized based on your interests \u2014 wine enthusiasts might want to spend more time in Kakheti, while adventure seekers could add rafting or paragliding. Georgia rewards the curious traveler with unexpected discoveries around every corner.'
